author: news.com.au
title: Stocks to watch at noon on Tuesday
text:
STOCKS to watch on the Australian stock exchange at noon on Tuesday:
AMC - AMCOR - up 8.00 cents, or 1.29 per cent, at $6.29
Packaging giant Amcor is continuing to expand operations in India, acquiring Packaging India Private Ltd (PIPL) for $US26.4 million ($A35.65 million). CSR - CSR - up 5.00 cents, or 1.43 per cent, at $3.55 Building products supplier CSR says its outlook is positive as housing starts look to climb to record levels, with more than 200,000 expected in fiscal 2016. MDC - MEDLAB CLINICAL - up 0.5 cents, or 2.5 per cent, at 20.5 cents Nutritional pharmaceutical researcher Medlab Clinical has list on the ASX. NRT - NOVOGEN - up 1.5 cents, or 6.38 per cent, at 25 cents Novogen shares have leapt by more than 10 per cent in early trade after studies involving one of the biotech's drugs indicates it may improve the effectiveness of chemotherapy in children. RAP - RESAPP - up 0.07 cents, or 3.13 per cent, at 2.2 cents Tech health company ResApp, which holds the exclusive license to develop an app based on technology funded by Bill and Melinda Gates, has enjoyed a solid re-entry to the Australian share market. WBC - WESTPAC BANKING CORPORATION - up 60 cents, or 1.82 per cent, at $33.56 Westpac will delay the planned sale of its banking operations in Vanuatu and Solomon Islands.
